            "Desc": "Cold and solid scales from a Solitary Suanni. They retain pure adeptal energy even after falling off and cannot be damaged by ordinary weapons.<br>Ordinary beasts can sometimes be affected by errant adeptal energy and become more powerful than usual. However, a suanni's adeptal energy originates from within themselves, which is why their leader is often regarded as equal to adepti.<br>Despite being considered auspicious beasts, there are nearly-forgotten legends of a suanni named \"the mountain lord\" attacking villages. The Wushou Dance was thought to have originated from a ritual to appease said being. However, since very few people have seen a suanni at all, the theory naturally cannot be verified.",
